  "description": [
    "Friday 11 January 1963 Nuclear Powered Submarine To Be Launched 12 Jan Two American Presidents will be honored simultaneously at Portsmouth Naval Shipyard 12 January The greatgreat grand daughter of one of the Presidents launches the Navys 17th Polaris ballistic submarine the nuclear powered John Adams The second ballistic missile sub marine to be built at the ship yard the ship is named for Presi dents John Adams and his son John Quincy Adams Mrs James C Abigail Adams Manny President John Quincy Adams gnatgreat granddaugh ter will launch the ship Principal speaker for the launching cere mony will be Mr Thomas B Adams a member of the Shera ton Corp of America He is a di rect descendant of President John Adams A 7000ton submarine of the Lafayette class John Adams will be the Navys largest submarine Capable of firing the 2500mile advanced Polaris A3 ballistic missile the submarines keel was laid 6 February 1961 Commis sioning of the John Adams is scheduled for this Fall Springboard 63 Underway In Caribbean Nineteen Newport based de strovers are among 110 Atlantic Fleet ships p a r t i c i p a t i n g in Springboard 63 in"
